texts: Generalized bone loss pattern with 30–40% reduction in the posterior mandible. Defects are mostly horizontal with a few vertical pockets near 16 and 26. No furcation involvement visible.
CBCT shows a well-defined periapical radiolucency of 4.2 mm at 21 apex. Buccal cortical plate thinning. No sinus involvement. Canal curvature moderate. Additional lateral canal visible.
Horizontal impaction of 38 with direct contact to the mandibular canal. OPG-style slice shows narrowing of canal. Follicular radiolucency 3 mm. Root of 37 exhibits mild resorption.

Patient undergoing implant evaluation for 36 region. Bone height 11.2 mm, width 6.1 mm. Mandibular canal located 3.2 mm inferiorly. Density mostly D2–D3. No pathology. Adequate space for 4.3 mm implant.
Implant planning for 46 region shows reduced vertical height of 7.5 mm with sinus pneumatization. Bone density D3. Canal safe distance 2.1 mm. Sinus lift recommended prior to implant placement.

Endodontic CBCT Guidelines:
- Evaluate canal curvature and calcification.
- Identify additional canals (MB2, DL canals, etc.).
- Check proximity of apex to sinus/mandibular canal.
- Assess periapical radiolucency: size, borders, cortical breach.
- Observe vertical root fractures, cracks, post position.
- Identify perfusion, ledges, missed canals.

Impacted Tooth CBCT Guidelines:
- Classification of impaction: mesioangular, distoangular, horizontal, vertical.
- Evaluate relation to mandibular canal.
- Check crown-root resorption of adjacent teeth.
- Look for follicular radiolucency.
- Identify buccal/lingual position.
- Assess available space and angulation.

Implant CBCT Evaluation Guidelines:
- Minimum bone height recommended: 8–10 mm.
- Minimum bone width recommended: 5–6 mm.
- Maintain 2 mm safety distance from the mandibular canal.
- Assess cortical bone thickness.
- Check maxillary sinus floor proximity and pneumatization.
- Look for sinus septa before sinus lift.
- Evaluate bone density pattern: D1–D4 classification.
